{
  "texts": [
    "In the domain of 3D shape analysis, AEs learn compressed representations for tasks like shape generation, completion, and retrieval.",
    "Achieving a disentangled latent representation that separates various factors of variation is a challenge.",
    "Recent research introduces methods like Split-AE (Saha et al. 2022) and 3D Shape Variational Autoencoder Latent Disentanglement (Foti et al. 2022), addressing this challenge.",
    "Other approaches employ deep learning features for 3D shape retrieval by projecting 3D shapes into 2D space and utilizing AEs for feature learning (Zhu et al. 2016).",
    "Additionally, architectures like pointcloud AEs combined with VAEs are explored to partition the latent space and enhance 3D shape analysis (Aumentado-Armstrong et al. 2019)."
  ]
}